{"article_id":"erp22R3nuTQCnYdm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The Supreme Court refused Monday to review a federal judge 's order","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that the Trump administration continue a program","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"protecting undocumented immigrants","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"brought to the United States as children .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"The denial leaves in place the popular DACA program ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"which has protected some 690,000 undocumented immigrants from deportation","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"and enabled them to get work permits .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"The program had faced a March 5 deadline for congressional action","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"set by Trump last summer .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Two federal courts have ruled","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"the administration 's action was illegal .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"The justices could have agreed to hear the case this spring ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"leapfrogging a federal appeals court","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"based in California","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"that has been sympathetic to the cause of immigrants .","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"They also could have overruled federal District Judge William Alsup","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"without a hearing .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Instead , they simply allowed the case to run its normal course through the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 9th Circuit .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"`` It is assumed that the Court of Appeals will proceed expeditiously","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"to decide this case , ''","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"the justices said","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"in denying the Trump administration 's petition .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"The case still could come to the high court in the future .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"The action represents a temporary victory for the young adults","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"brought to the U.S. illegally by their parents or guardians under the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"established by President Barack Obama in 2012 .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"And it represents a major setback for the Trump administration ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"which vowed to continue the legal battle in the lower courts .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"`` We will continue to defend DHS ' lawful authority","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"to wind down DACA in an orderly manner , ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Department of Justice spokesman Devin O'Malley said in a statement Monday .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Trump said during remarks before a meeting with governors Monday","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"that `` we 'll see what happens .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"That 's my attitude . ''","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"California Attorney General Xavier Becerra ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"who led one of the lawsuits","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"challenging the Trump administration ' s termination of DACA ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Monday ' s decision by the high court will provide much-needed relief to DACA enrollees , the companies","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"they work for","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"and the schools","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"they attend .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"\" DACA is fully legal , ''","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Becerra said .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"\" The Trump administration ' s attempts","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"to end it","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"were fully illegal .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"And we hope","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that this has become clearer at each step of the way . \"","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"More :","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"What the Supreme Court ruling means for DACA and almost 700,000 undocumented immigrants","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"More :","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"Trump administration will ask Supreme Court to reverse DACA ruling","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"The dispute dates back to 2012 ,","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"when Obama established the program","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"without congressional action .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"The goal was to protect from deportation undocumented immigrants","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"who were brought to the country as children ,","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"but many Republicans called it executive overreach","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"and have remained opposed to the program .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Trump vowed to end the program on the campaign trail ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"but seemed to change his mind","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"after winning election .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"He went back and forth over the future of DACA during his first months in office ,","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"but made his decision in September :","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"he announced","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that the program would end ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"but not until March 5 ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"giving Congress six months","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"to find a solution .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Democrats and Republicans have been squabbling over the fate of those so-called DREAMers ever since .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"Democrats want the program left alone","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"or made permanent through a new law ;","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Republicans , with Trump 's backing , have demanded other immigration enforcement and border security enhancements in exchange ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"including an expansion of the wall along the Mexican border .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"The negotiations have been tense ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"even leading to a three-day government shutdown in January","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"as Democrats briefly demanded a DACA solution as part of a spending bill .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"now that the Supreme Court has decided not to fast-track the legal battle ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"the program will continue allowing DACA recipients to renew their protections .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"That eliminates the deadline","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"faced by Congress .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"The case now goes back to the 9th Circuit ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"which must consider the ruling from Alsup","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"that preserved DACA .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"In his ruling last month , Alsup granted a request by California , the University of California system , and several California cities to block Trump 's decision","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"to end the DACA program","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"while their lawsuit","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"challenging the program 's termination","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"plays out in court .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"those already approved for protection and work permits","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"must be allowed to renew them","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"before they expire .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"Alsup said","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"the challengers were likely to succeed","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"by claiming","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that the Trump administration 's decision","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"to end the program","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"was `` arbitrary and capricious ''","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"and based on a flawed legal premise .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"the plaintiffs would be harmed , in part through economic disruptions and the loss of tax revenue","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"caused by the DREAMers ' change in status .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Earlier this month , federal District Judge Nicholas Garaufis issued a similar ruling in New York .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"the administration was wrong for several reasons , such as its premise","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"that Obama 's creation of the program was unconstitutional and illegal in the first place .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"`` Any of these flaws would support invalidating the DACA rescission as arbitrary and capricious , ''","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Garaufis ruled .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":223,"left":0,"right":222,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":222,"left":164,"right":221,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":160,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":134,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":120,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":118,"right":119,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":115,"right":117,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":1,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":2,"right":113,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":5,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":119,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":23,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":121,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":131,"left":126,"right":130,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":124,"right":125,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":12,"right":123,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":122,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"le